<p><strong>If you're aware of any adaptations, fanworks, what-have-you that aren't on this list, feel free to edit them in.</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TheeSherm has done a reading of <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QCWqndzIllw&amp;t=2s">Your Call Is Important To Us</a>. I'm quite impressed that he was able to do so many voices and keep them all straight.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLrzSbvG1Ff_BXhk4tEm-mRzS-pQ835BbS">Here's</a> a playlist of Herman Fuller readings by <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCo8wcw_ey4zR5nBn6yPZIzg">TheRandomzJake</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/SCPFoundationSCPs3000To3999">SCP-3440</a> has an entry on tv tropes, and the events of Dread &amp; Circuses appear to be referenced under the <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Characters/SCPFoundationGroups">GoI page</a> as well.</li>
<li>And, as previously mentioned, <a href="https://hisclockworkservants.tumblr.com/post/172857538495/what-do-you-think-dread-circus-characters-look">them as buns</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608430610" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;">SunnyClockwork</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
